Event Description: Captures every time a new mobile is associated with an IMSI Event Trigger: Triggered the first time when an IMSI is associated with a new UE Context, at reception of RANAP Common Id after successful RRC Connection Setup or at reception of IMSI in RANAP Relocation Request at incoming Hard Handover. When the feature FAJ 121 2267: Differentiated UE Handling is activated the triggering of the event is delayed until the IMEI-SV is available after reception of the RRC Uplink Direct Transfer containing the NAS message Identity Response .

This event is captured whenever a radio measurement report is received in UEH. Note: currently this event is not triggered in TD. See FDI 11/19024-11/FCP 103 6856 TD-SCDMA FDI: Power Control On DCH in RNC .
event.rncfunction: Pwr Ctrl Dedicated Channels in RNC
event.cpitext: Captured whenever a radio measurement report is received in the RNC subsystem UE Handling (UEH). The parameter values EVENT_VALUE_UL_SIR_ERROR (0) and EVENT_VALUE_DL_TX_CODE_POWER (1) apply to the parameter EVENT_PARAM_MEASURED_ENTITY for this event.

event.triggerdescription: This event is captured whenever a radio measurement report is received in RNH.
event.rncfunction: "Power control common channel, Admission Control, Congestion Control"
event.cpitext: Captured whenever a radio measurement report is received in the RNC subsystem Radio Network Handling (RNH). The parameter values EVENT_VALUE_UL_INTERFERENCE (2), EVENT_VALUE_ DL_TX_CARRIER_POWER (3), EVENT_VALUE_NON_HS_POWER (4) and EVENT_VALUE_HSDSCH_REQUIRED_POWER (5) apply to the parameter EVENT_PARAM_MEASURED_ENTITY for this event.

event.cpitext: Captured whenever the congestion control function switches any user channels or terminates any connections. The EVENT_PARAM_SOURCE_C_ID_1_SECONDARY_SERV_HSDSCH_CELL is reported as not applicable because proper information is not available in this situation.

event.triggerdescription: This event is captured whenever transmitted carrier power and/or UL interference exceed their respective threshold values.
event.cpitext: Captured whenever transmitted carrier power or uplink interference exceeds its respective threshold value. Either of the parameters EVENT_PARAM_DL_POWER or EVENT_PARAM_UL_INTERFERENCE reports a measurement value. The parameter EVENT_PARAM_DL_POWER reports a measurement value if the cell goes into downlink congestion; otherwise, it is reported as an invalid value. The parameter EVENT_PARAM_UL_INTERFERENCE reports a measurement value if the cell goes into uplink congestion; otherwise, it is reported as an invalid value.

event.triggerdescription: This event is captured whenever both transmitted carrier power and UL interference have moved below their respective threshold values after at least one of them being above...
event.cpitext: Captured whenever transmitted carrier power or uplink interference falls below its respective threshold value. Either of the parameters EVENT_PARAM_DL_POWER or EVENT_PARAM_UL_INTERFERENCE reports a measurement value. The parameter EVENT_PARAM_DL_POWER reports a measurement value if the cell exits downlink congestion; otherwise it is reported as an invalid value. The parameter EVENT_PARAM_UL_INTERFERENCE reports a measurement value if the cell exits uplink congestion; otherwise it is reported as an invalid value.

event.cpitext: Captured whenever one of the conditions listed for parameter EVENT_PARAM_EVENT_TRIGGER occurs. The event is sent for each code tree node that is changed.

event.triggerdescription: The event is captured when any of the event triggers occur in the Radio Connection Supervision algorithm, including both High Speed (HS) connections and non HS connections. If an event trigger means hat both RCS algorithms are affected (HS and non-HS RCS algorithm), only one GPEH event is generated.
event.cpitext: This event is reported in relation to the Radio Connection Supervision algorithms for UE. It is reported for events in the RCS algorithms for UE when in CELL_FACH and CELL_DCH states. Furthermore, when in CELL_DCH, it is reported for the separate algorithms used for connections using an HS-DSCH channel as well as when not using this channel. The following conditions must be considered: -When in CELL_DCH , a received trigger may be used as a trigger for both the HS and non-HS RCS algorithms. In such cases, only one GPEH event is generated even though both algorithms are affected. -At timeout of the RCS timer supervising an HS- DSCH connection, the GPEH event indicates the action OVERALL_CONNECTION_RELEASE, even though the action taken by the algorithm is a signalling connection release towards the PS Core Network (CN). -The event can monitor both RNSAP logical errors and the RNSAP protocol message itself but it must be activate to monitor RNSAP syntactical errors.

One event is triggered per CN node if system release conditions are applicable.

event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Captured for each failed CS or PS call setup attempt. Event Trigger: Triggered either at sending of RAB Assignment Response indicating failure to setup or modify RABs or when a signalling connection is released and the release is not a normal release. A call setup attempt can be detected from the establishment cause in RRC Connection Request, Cell Update or Initial Direct Transfer or through reception of RAB Assignment Request with the IE RABs to be setup or modifi Triggered for each failed CS or PS call setup attempt when one of the following conditions is met: - Failure to establish RRC Connection after RRC Connection Request for a CS or PS call setup attempt (1, 2) - System-initiated release (3) of a signaling connection during the NAS signaling sequence (4) at call setup towards a CS or PS CN (1, 2), if an RRC Connection Request, Cell Update or Initial Direct Transfer containing the IE 'establisment cause' was received prior to the NAS signaling sequence. - RANAP Rab Assignment Response message sent to the CN indicating failure to setup or modify RABs. (1) A call setup attempt towards the CS CN has RRC establishment cause equal to 'Emergency Call', 'Originating', 'Originating Conversational Call' or 'Terminating Conversational Call'. (2) A call setup attempt towards the PS CN has RRC establishment cause equal to 'Originating Interactive Call', 'Terminating Interactive Call', 'Originating Background Call', 'Terminating Background Call' or 'Originating Subscribed Traffic Call'. (3) A system-initiated release can be triggered by: - a RANAP Reset message received from the CN; - a RANAP Iu Release Command message received from the CN with 'release cause' set to anything other than 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', 'User Inactivity' or 'no-remaining-rab'; - a RAB Assignment Request message received from the CN with 'release cause' set to anything other than 'Normal Release', 'Successful Relocation', 'Resource Optimisation Relocation', or 'User Inactivity'; - the RNC when sending a RANAP Reset Resource message to the CN; - detection in the RNC of RANAP Service Unavailable. (4) The NAS signaling sequence is defined as the phase starting with IU Signaling Connection establishment and ending with RAB Assignment Request. One event is triggered per CN node if system release conditions are applicable.
event.rncfunction: "Signalling Connection Handling, RAB Assigment Evaluation, CELL Update Iu RANAP Termination"

event.triggerdescription: The event is triggered everytime when RNC enter IFLS but RNC do not continue with an evaluation of the candidate cells and IFLS attempt stopped due to some reason
event.cpitext: The event is triggered every time when RNC enters Inter Frequency Load Sharing (IFLS) but RNC does not continue with an evaluation of the candidate cells and IFLS attempt stopped due to some reason.

event.triggerdescription: The event is triggered everytime RNC enter IFLS and evaluate the candidate cells that can attempt to load share to.
event.cpitext: The event is triggered every time RNC enters Inter Frequency Load Sharing (IFLS) and evaluates the candidate cells that can attempt to load share.

event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Captured when the ANR feature is prevented from adding a Neighbour Cell Relation in the MOM. Event Trigger: Triggered when the ANR feature is prevented from adding a Neighbour Cell Relation in the MOM, see RAN CPI ANR Mobility, 183/1553-HSD 101 02.

The event is triggered when the amount of bad CRCs during a predefined sliding window exceeds a predefined value. The event is only visible if MRR-W (FAJ 121 993) and UE Quality Measurement Event 5A (FAJ121 3930) optional features are available.
event.osscomments: Not displayed in the PMS GUI! Only as part of the UE Quality Measurement Event 5A

event.triggerdescription: Provided that the license for Automatically Triggered Access Class Barring on Cell Level (FAJ 121 3946) is active and UtranCell::autoAcbEnabled = TRUE, this event is triggered at a periodicity given as a multiple of 10 seconds, where the multiplicity can be 1-6 times.
event.rncfunction: Automatically Triggered Access Class Barring on Cell Level
event.cpitext: Event is triggered at a periodicity given as a multiple of 10 seconds, where the multiplicity can be 1-6 times.

event.triggerdescription: The event shall be triggered for any successful case between the following points for a Hard Handover (IRATHO/CC, IFHO, CNHHO):
event.rncfunction: IRAT Handover IRAT Cell Change CN Hard handover Inter-Frequency Handover
event.cpitext: The event is triggered for any successful case between the following points for a Hard Handover (IRATHO/CC, IFHO, CNHHO): Execution proposal from Handover evaluation -> Termination of procedure.

event.triggerdescription: Event Description: Capture power save actions by the RNC feature Traffic Aware Power Save. Event Trigger: The event is triggered when the RNC Traffic Aware Power Save feature has: - locked a UtranCell - unlocked a UtranCell - aborted an ongoing feature locking of a UtranCell prior to completion

parameter.paramdescription: In case the reported shape is Ellipsoid Point with Uncertainly circle, this parameter shall be set equal to the coded uncertainty radius of that shape.
parameter.paramcomments: For INTERNAL_UE_POSITIONING_QOS
parameter.cpitext: If the Cell Id method is selected, this parameter is calculated based on the estimated Cell Id area; in other words, equal to round(ln(1+1/10*sqrt (area/pi))/ln(1.1)). If the A-GPS method is selected this parameter is equal to the calculated uncertaintyCode or horizontalUncertainty parameters. If neither of these parameters are available, the event parameter must be set to invalid.

parameter.paramdescription: Longitude degrees of the antenna where the RTT measurement is made. If Longitude sign is equal to East, the Longitude value (N) is derived by the formula N = (2^24)*(X/360) N+1, where X is the longitude in degrees (0..180). If Longitude sign is equal to West, the Longitude value (N) is derived by the formula N = (2^24)*(-X/360) N+1, where X is the longitude in degrees (-180..0).

If Longitude sign is equal to West, the Longitude value (N) is derived by the formula N = (2^24)*(-X/360) N+1, where X is the longitude in degrees (-180..0). parameter.paramdescription: In general the HO type is determined by the combination of the parameters EVENT_PARAM_EVALUATION_CASE and EVENT_PARAM_PROCEDURE_INDICATOR. For applicable parameter values, see their respective parameter description. Parameter representation for IRATHO: This parameter represents RSSI (Range: 0..63, Resolution: See 3GPP spec, Unit: See 3GPP spec). 3GPP spec 45.008 specifies the mapping between the reported value and the actual physical measured value, where RXLEV corresponds to RSSI. The measured signal level shall be mapped to an RXLEV value between 0 and 63, as follows (where SCALE equals '0' when ordering a 3a measurement, therefore excluded below): RXLEV 0 = less than 110dBm RXLEV 1 = 110dBm to 109dBm RXLEV 2 = 109dBm to 108dBm : : RXLEV 62 = 49dBm to 48dBm RXLEV 63 = greater than 48dBm Parameter representation for IRATCC: This parameter represents RSSI. Same definition as for IRATHO Parameter representation for GAN HO: This parameter represents RSSI. Same definition as for IRATHO Parameter representation for CNHHO: This parameter represents CPICH Ec/N0 (Range: 0..49, Resolution: 0.5, Unit: dB (the physical measured value is in dB). See 3GPP spec 25.133 for mapping between reported value and the actual physical measured value. The reporting range is for CPICH Ec/Eo is from -24 ...0 dB, resolution 0.5.) Parameter representation for IFHO: This parameter represents CPICH Ec/N0. Same definition as for CNHHO.
parameter.paramcomments: Introduced in rev. BM, W10:I3 by FDI 13/19024-10/FCP1038812

parameter.paramdescription: The last capabilities evaluated by IFLS. This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 7 bits (LSB) are used, the rest are spare. For details on bitfield defintions, check the EventParamBitfieldDef sheet.
parameter.paramcomments: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED! Introduced in W13B Sprint 13w20 rev CX by PSS 97/102 68-FCP 121 7060 - Interf Frequency Load Sharing
parameter.cpitext: The last capabilities evaluated by IFLS. This parameter is presented as a bit map value. Only the first 9 bits (LSB) are used, the rest is spare. Bit 0 indicates if MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 1 indicates if Dual-band MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No Dual-band Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=Dual-band Multi Carrier evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 2 indicates if MIMO is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No MMO evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=MMO evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 3 indicates if EUL is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No EUL evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=EUL evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 4 indicates if HS is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No HS evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=HS evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 5 indicates if CPC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No CPC evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=CPC evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 6 indicates if 64QAM is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No 64QAM evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=64QAM evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 7 indicates if 3MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No 3MC evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=3MC evaluation during HS IFLS. Bit 8 indicates if Dual-band 3MC is lastly evaluated during HS IFLS: 0=No Dual-band 3MC evaluation during HS IFLS, 1=Dual-band 3MC evaluation during HS IFLS. Bits 9-15 are spare and is always be 0.

parameter.paramdescription: International Mobile Equipment Identity Software Version IMEI-SV is built up by 16 digits in BCD (Binary Coded Decimal) format, each digit represented by 4 bits, Digit 1 is the MSD (Most Significant Digit = leftmost Digit) and Digit 16 is the LSD (Least Significant Digit = rightmost Digit): - bit[60..63] = Digit 1, where bit[63] is the leftmost bit and also the Most Significant Bit (MSB) - bit[56..59] = Digit 2 - ... - bit[0..3] = Digit 16, where bit[0] is the rightmost bit and also the Least Significant Bit (LSB)
parameter.paramcomments: Introduced in W13A 12W24, 10/.. CM by PSS 18/102 68-FCP 121 7060 Uen Differentiated UE Handling Modified in W15A, Sprint 14w37, 10/..B CPI update, PSS: 248/10268-FCP1217060.

parameter.paramdescription: International Mobile Subscriber Identity IMSI is built up by 15 digits in BCD (Binary Coded Decimal) format, each digit represented by 4 bits, where Digit 1 is the MSD (Most Significant Digit = leftmost Digit) and Digit 15 is the LSD (Least Significant Digit = rightmost Digit): - bit[56..59] = Digit 1, where bit[59] is the leftmost bit and also the Most Significant Bit (MSB) - bit[52..55] = Digit 2 - ... - bit[0..3] = Digit 15, where bit[0] is the rightmost bit and also the Least Significant Bit (LSB)
parameter.paramcomments: Description clarified in W13A 12W24, 10/.. CM Modified in W15A, 14w37 sprint, 10/..B, PSS: 248/10268-FCP1217060
parameter.cpitext: International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI), 15 digits BCD , each digit represented by 4 bits. IMSI, BCD encoded, digits 1-15: bits 56-59=most sign digit (Digit 1), ..., bits 0-3=least sign digit (Digit 15). Most Significant Digit (MSD)=leftmost digit (Digit 1); Most Significant Bit (MSB)=leftmost bit (bit position 59). EVENT_PARAM_IMSI = EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_1 + EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_2. EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_1 (32 bits) is the left 8 digits of IMSI in BCD format, digits 1-8: bits 28-31=most sign digit (Digit 1), ..., bits 0-3=least sign digit (Digit 8). Most Significant Digit (MSD)=leftmost digit (Digit 1). Most Significant Bit (MSB)=leftmost bit (bit position 31). EVENT_PARAM_IMSI_2 (32 bits) is the right 7 digits of IMSI in BCD format, digits 9-15: bits 28-31=padding bits, bits 24-27=most sign digit (Digit 9), ..,bits 0-3 = least sign digit (Digit 15). Most Significant Digit (MSD)=leftmost digit (Digit 9); Most Significant Bit (MSB)=leftmost bit (bit position 31).

parameter.paramcomments: Changed due to W11: EG6+ 156/190 24-FCP 101 8201,
parameter.cpitext: Measured value for the related measurement type according to the parameter EVENT_PARAM_MEASURED_ENTITY (SIR error, DL Tx code power, UL interference, DL Tx CarrierPower, Non HighSpeed Power, HSDSCH Required Power). See 3GPP TS 25.133 for updated definitions. The figures here are taken from 3GPP TS 25.133 V5.17.0 (2005-12), 25133-5h0. Ranges for the reported values per measurement type are as follows: SIR Error range: 0..125 (measurement range -31..31, unit: dB, resolution: 0.5) DL Tx code power, range: 0..127 (measurement range -10..46, unit: dBm, resolution: 0.5. Any Invalid Parameter A parameter without a valid value to report at the time of event reporting is filled with 1s, also referred to as the value EVENT_VALUE_INVALID. A parameter does not have to have any value to report. This happens either when no value is applicable to the event, or there is no value available at the time of event reporting. Most parameter have an extra bit (the most significant bit, that is, the leftmost one) in addition to what is required for the parameter value range called the validity bit. It is used together with the second most significant bit to indicate whether the parameter value is Available / Not Available or Not Applicable. If the two most significant bits are 11, the value is interpreted as Not Applicable. If the two most significant bits are 10, the value is interpreted as Not Available. With a 3-bit parameter (including one validity bit), the parameter value range of 0..3, the following applies: -Not Applicable = 111 -Not Available = 100

parameter.paramdescription: The scanner ID field consists of sequence of bits (24bits), each bit corresponding to a particular scanner ID (023 scanners GPEH, 0..15 scanners UETR, 0-1 scanners CTR). Sc. ID 1..24 (1= bit0... 24= bit23) Bit pos MSB 23, 22, 21 ... 2, 1, 0 LSB 0 is used in the corresponding bit location to indicate when an event is NOT part of a particular scanner. 1 will be used in the corresponding bit location to indicate that an event is part of a particular scanner. Note that the same event could be part of one, several, or all scanners. Event presence for each scanner will be indicated with 1 in the scanner ID field.

parameter.paramdescription: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 16 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used. Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CMin UL used.Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI(default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI. Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 indicates if 64QAM is activated: 0 = 64QAM not activated, 1 = 64QAM activated. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech categor y, where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern 00) 1=AMR-NB MMMulti-rate. (bit pattern 01 ) 2=AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern 10), 3=AMR NB MM Set to 1, (bit pattern 11 ). Bit 7 is reserved if MIMO is activated; 0=MIMO deactivated, 1=MIMO activated. Bit 8 indicates if SrbOnHs is used: 0 = SRB on X/DCH, 1 =SRB on X/HS. Bit 9 indicates if SrbOnEul is used: 0 = SRB on DCH/X, 1 =SRB on EUL/X. Bit 10 indicates if Multi Carrier is used/activated: 0= Multi Carrier is not used/activated, 1= Multi Carrier is used/activated. Bit 11 indicates if High Speed Downlink for FACH is used: 0 =HS-FACH is not used, 1 = HS-FACH is used. Bit 12 indicates if CPC is used: 0=CPC not used, 1=CPC used. Bit 13 indicates if Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used/activated: 0 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is not used, 1 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used. Bit 14 indicates if Enhanced UE DRX is used/activated: 0 = Enhanced UE DRX is not used, 1 = Enhanced UE DRX is used. Bit 15 indicates if the connection is using IL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-e/es used on E-DCH (non-IL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-i/is on E-DCH (IL2). NOTE 1: If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. NOTE 2: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED!
parameter.paramcomments: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED! Introduced in rev. AX, P7:I2 by FDI 12/19024-10/FCP1036503. Introduced meaning for bit 3 in rev. BB, P7MD:I5, FDI 53/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 4 (the 5th LSB bit) for 64QAM usage indication in rev. BC, P7:I6, CR WRNae01539. Reserved Bit 5,6 (the 6th, 7th LSB bit) for Coverage based AMR in rev. BC2, P7:I6, FDI 95/19024-10/FCP1036503. and TR WRNae16065 Reserved Bit 7 (the 8th LSB bit) for MIMO in rev. BD, P7:I8, FDI 68/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 8 (the 9th LSB bit) for ROHC in rev. BD, P7:I9, FDI 56/19024-10/FCP1036503. Bit 12 introduced CPC usage introduced by FDI CPC for battery in Wanessa RNC: 38/190 24-10/FCP 103 8812 W10B:NI7 GA change due to TR WRNae69399 W11 EG2 rev BV: change due to FDI: 7/19024-FCP1018201, Node FDI 64QAM and MIMO Combination in W11 RNC W11 EG4 rev BZ: change due to FDI: 3. FDI: 5/190 24-FCP 101 8201, Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier in Willow RNC W12A rev CF: change due to FDI: 1. FDI 146/190 24-FCP 101 8201, Node FDI Battery efficiency for high speed FACH Bit 14 added! W12 EG4 rev CG1: FDI 3/190 24-FCP 121 3051, Node FDI Improved L2 for W12 RNC introduced bit 15 use added. W12B EG4 rev CG2: change due to CR: 136/... bit-field definitions introduced W13B sprint 12W48 rev CT: change due to PSS: 83/102 68-FCP 121 7060, AMR NB MM multi-rate-set 1 Modified in W15A, Sprint 14w37, 10/..B CPI update PSS: 248/10268-FCP1217060.

parameter.paramdescription: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 16 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used. Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CMin UL used.Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI(default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI. Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 indicates if 64QAM is activated: 0 = 64QAM not activated, 1 = 64QAM activated. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech categor y, where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern 00) 1=AMR-NB MMMulti-rate. (bit pattern 01 ) 2=AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern 10), 3=AMR NB MM Set to 1, (bit pattern 11 ). Bit 7 is reserved if MIMO is activated; 0=MIMO deactivated, 1=MIMO activated. Bit 8 indicates if SrbOnHs is used: 0 = SRB on X/DCH, 1 =SRB on X/HS. Bit 9 indicates if SrbOnEul is used: 0 = SRB on DCH/X, 1 =SRB on EUL/X. Bit 10 indicates if Multi Carrier is used/activated: 0= Multi Carrier is not used/activated, 1= Multi Carrier is used/activated. Bit 11 indicates if High Speed Downlink for FACH is used: 0 =HS-FACH is not used, 1 = HS-FACH is used. Bit 12 indicates if CPC is used: 0=CPC not used, 1=CPC used. Bit 13 indicates if Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used/activated: 0 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is not used, 1 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used. Bit 14 indicates if Enhanced UE DRX is used/activated: 0 = Enhanced UE DRX is not used, 1 = Enhanced UE DRX is used. Bit 15 indicates if the connection is using IL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-e/es used on E-DCH (non-IL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-i/is on E-DCH (IL2). NOTE 1: If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. NOTE 2: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED!
parameter.paramcomments: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED! Introduced in rev. AX, P7:I2 by FDI 12/19024-10/FCP1036503. Introduced meaning for bit 3 in rev. BB, P7MD:I5, FDI 53/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 4 (the 5th LSB bit) for 64QAM usage indication in rev. BC, P7:I6, CR WRNae01539. Reserved Bit 5,6 (the 6th, 7th LSB bit) for Coverage based AMR in rev. BC2, P7:I6, FDI 95/19024-10/FCP1036503. and TR WRNae16065 Reserved Bit 7 (the 8th LSB bit) for MIMO in rev. BD, P7:I8, FDI 68/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 8 (the 9th LSB bit) for ROHC in rev. BD, P7:I9, FDI 56/19024-10/FCP1036503. Bit 12 introduced CPC usage introduced by FDI CPC for battery in Wanessa RNC: 38/190 24-10/FCP 103 8812 Modified in rev BT, W10:I6 by FDI Inter-Frequency Loadsharing: 37/190 24-10/FCP 103 8812 W10B:NI7 GA change due to TR WRNae69399 W11 EG2 rev BV: change due to FDI: 7/19024-FCP1018201, Node FDI 64QAM and MIMO Combination in W11 RNC W11 EG4 rev BZ: change due to FDI: 3. FDI: 5/190 24-FCP 101 8201, Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier in Willow RNC W12A rev CF: change due to FDI: 1. FDI 146/190 24-FCP 101 8201, Node FDI Battery efficiency for high speed FACH Bit 14 added! W12 EG4 rev CG1: FDI 3/190 24-FCP 121 3051, Node FDI Improved L2 for W12 RNC introduced bit 15 use added W12B EG4 rev CG2: change due to CR: 136/... bit-field definitions introduced W13B sprint 12W48 rev CT: change due to PSS: 83/102 68-FCP 121 7060, AMR NB MM multi-rate-set 1 Modified in W15A, Sprint 14w37, 10/..B CPI update PSS: 248/10268-FCP1217060.

parameter.cpitext: The capabilities of UE related to IFLS. This parameter is presented as a bit map value. Only the first 9 bits (LSB) are used, the rest are spare. Bit 0 indicates if UE is capable of Multi Carrier: 0=Not Multi Carrier Capable UE, 1=Multi Carrier Capable UE. Bit 1 indicates if UE is capable of Dual-band Multi Carrier: 0=Not Dual-band Multi Carrier Capable UE, 1=Dual-band Multi Carrier Capable UE. Bit 2 indicates if UE is capable of MIMO: 0=Not MMO capable UE, 1=MMO capable UE. Bit 3 indicates if UE is capable of EUL: 0=Not EUL capable UE, 1=EUL capable UE. Bit 4 indicates if UE is capable of HS: 0=Not HS capable UE, 1=HS capable UE. Bit 5 indicates if UE is capable of CPC: 0=Not CPC capable UE, 1=CPC capable UE. Bit 6 indicates if UE is capable of 64QAM: 0=Not CPC capable UE, 1=Not 64QAM capable UE. Bit 7 indicates if UE is capable of 3 Multi Carrier: 0=Not 3 Multi Carrier capable UE, 1=3 Multi Carrier: capable UE. Bit 8 indicates if UE is capable of Dual-band 3 Multi Carrier : 0=Not Dual-band 3 Multi Carrier capable UE, 1=Dual-band 3 Multi Carrier capable UE. Bits 9-15 are spare and is always 0.

parameter.paramdescription: This parameter is related to EVENT_PARAM_FAILURE. That parameter specifies the type of failure and this parameter the corresponding value for the failure. Possible values for differend failure reasons: - cngstState = range: [UL, DL, UL+DL], - totAseUl = Uplink ASE load in the cell, range: 0 - 2000, - totAseDl = Downlink ASE load in the cell, range: 0 - 2000], - current SF = range: [8, 16, 32], - dlChCodeTreeUsage = Number of links with SF = x in the cell, range: 0-x, - (filteredDlPower+estimatedDlPwrDelta) - Consumed DL capacity credits if blocked by DL RBS HW resources or UL and DL RBS HW resources. Range: 0 - 131071. - Consumed UL capacity credits if blocked due to only UL RBS HW resources. Range: 0 - 131071. - EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_USERS_ON_HSPDSCH Range: 0 - 1000. - Represents the number of E-DCH users in the serving cell in case of failure reason=EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_SERVING_CELL_USERS_EUL. Range: 0 - 100. - Represents the number of E-DCH users in the non-serving cell in case of failure reason=EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_NON_SERVING_CELL_USERS_EUL. Range: 0 - 100. - EVENT_VALUE_BLOCKED_BY_CONGESTION_CTRL. Range: 1-9, where: 1 = UL_OVERLOAD 2 = DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 3 = UL_AND_DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 4 = HSDSCH_OVERLOAD 5 = UL_AND_HSDSCH_OVERLOAD 8 = HSDSCH_AND_DL_DCH_OVERLOAD 9 = UL_AND_DL_DCH_AND_HSDSCH_OVERLOAD - TN_IUB failure reasons: Range 0..19900, Unit 100 kbit/s - Represents the number of radio links in case of failure reason=EVENT_VALUE_TOO_MANY_USERS_WITH_SFxx. Range: 0 - 256. SFxx = range: [4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128]

parameter.paramdescription: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 16 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used. Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CMin UL used.Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI(default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI. Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 indicates if 64QAM is activated: 0 = 64QAM not activated, 1 = 64QAM activated. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech categor y, where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern 00) 1=AMR-NB MMMulti-rate. (bit pattern 01 ) 2=AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern 10), 3=AMR NB MM Set to 1, (bit pattern 11 ). Bit 7 is reserved if MIMO is activated; 0=MIMO deactivated, 1=MIMO activated. Bit 8 indicates if SrbOnHs is used: 0 = SRB on X/DCH, 1 =SRB on X/HS. Bit 9 indicates if SrbOnEul is used: 0 = SRB on DCH/X, 1 =SRB on EUL/X. Bit 10 indicates if Multi Carrier is used/activated: 0= Multi Carrier is not used/activated, 1= Multi Carrier is used/activated. Bit 11 indicates if High Speed Downlink for FACH is used: 0 =HS-FACH is not used, 1 = HS-FACH is used. Bit 12 indicates if CPC is used: 0=CPC not used, 1=CPC used. Bit 13 indicates if Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used/activated: 0 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is not used, 1 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used. Bit 14 indicates if Enhanced UE DRX is used/activated: 0 = Enhanced UE DRX is not used, 1 = Enhanced UE DRX is used. Bit 15 indicates if the connection is using IL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-e/es used on E-DCH (non-IL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-i/is on E-DCH (IL2). NOTE 1: If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. NOTE 2: The Connection Properties of the UeRc reported in EVENT_PARAM_WANTED_CONF. This parameter is not applicable for IRATHO, IRATCC or GAN HO. For CNHHO this parameter shall report the Connection Properties of the wanted target UeRc for the CNHHO. NOTE 3: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED!
parameter.paramcomments: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED! Introduced in rev. BF, P7:I9 by FDI 99/19024-10/FCP1036504 Bit 12 introduced CPC usage introduced by FDI CPC for battery in Wanessa RNC: 38/190 24-10/FCP 103 8812 Modified in rev BT, W10:I6 by FDI Inter-Frequency Loadsharing: 37/190 24-10/FCP 103 8812 W10B:NI7 GA change due to TR WRNae69399 W11 EG2 rev BV: change due to FDI: 7/19024-FCP1018201, Node FDI 64QAM and MIMO Combination in W11 RNC W11 EG4 rev BZ: change due to FDI: 3. parameterext.name: EVENT_PARAM_SOURCE_CONNECTION_PROPERTIES
parameterext.paramextdescription: This parameter will be presented as a bit map value. Only the first 16 bits (LSB) are used. Bit 0 (LSB) indicates if CM in DL is used: 0=CM DL not used, 1=CM DL used. Bit 1 indicates if CM in UL is used: 0=CM UL not used, 1=CMin UL used.Bit 2 indicates TTI length if E-DCH is used: 0=10ms TTI(default value for non E-DCH connections), 1=2ms TTI. Bit 3 indicates if the connection is using EL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-hs used on HS-DSCH (non-EL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-ehs on HS-DSCH (EL2). Bit 4 indicates if 64QAM is activated: 0 = 64QAM not activated, 1 = 64QAM activated. Bits 5 and 6 are used to represent speech categor y, where: 0= Not applicable (bit pattern 00) 1=AMR-NB MMMulti-rate. (bit pattern 01 ) 2=AMR-NB MM Single-rate 12.2 (bit pattern 10), 3=AMR NB MM Set to 1, (bit pattern 11 ). Bit 7 is reserved if MIMO is activated; 0=MIMO deactivated, 1=MIMO activated. Bit 8 indicates if SrbOnHs is used: 0 = SRB on X/DCH, 1 =SRB on X/HS. Bit 9 indicates if SrbOnEul is used: 0 = SRB on DCH/X, 1 =SRB on EUL/X. Bit 10 indicates if Multi Carrier is used/activated: 0= Multi Carrier is not used/activated, 1= Multi Carrier is used/activated. Bit 11 indicates if High Speed Downlink for FACH is used: 0 =HS-FACH is not used, 1 = HS-FACH is used. Bit 12 indicates if CPC is used: 0=CPC not used, 1=CPC used. Bit 13 indicates if Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used/activated: 0 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is not used, 1 = Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier is used. Bit 14 indicates if Enhanced UE DRX is used/activated: 0 = Enhanced UE DRX is not used, 1 = Enhanced UE DRX is used. Bit 15 indicates if the connection is using IL2: 0=Fixed sizeRLC and MAC-e/es used on E-DCH (non-IL2), 1=Flexible or fixed size RLC and MAC-i/is on E-DCH (IL2). NOTE 1: If both Bit 4 and Bit 7 are active at the same time, the combination 64QAM+MIMO is used. NOTE 2: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED!
parameterext.paramextcomments: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED! Introduced in rev. AX, P7:I2 by FDI 12/19024-10/FCP1036503. Introduced meaning for bit 3 in rev. BB, P7MD:I5, FDI 53/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 4 (the 5th LSB bit) for 64QAM usage indication in rev. BC, P7:I6, CR WRNae01539. Reserved Bit 5,6 (the 6th, 7th LSB bit) for Coverage based AMR in rev. BC2, P7:I6, FDI 95/19024-10/FCP1036503. and TR WRNae16065 Reserved Bit 7 (the 8th LSB bit) for MIMO in rev. BD, P7:I8, FDI 68/19024-10/FCP1036503. Reserved Bit 8 (the 9th LSB bit) for ROHC in rev. BD, P7:I9, FDI 56/19024-10/FCP1036503. Bit 12 introduced CPC usage introduced by FDI CPC for battery in Wanessa RNC: 38/190 24-10/FCP 103 8812 W10B:NI7 GA change due to TR WRNae69399 W11 EG2 rev BV: change due to FDI: 7/19024-FCP1018201, Node FDI 64QAM and MIMO Combination in W11 RNC W11 EG4 rev BZ: change due to FDI: 3. FDI: 5/190 24-FCP 101 8201, Dual-Band HSDPA Multi-Carrier in Willow RNC W12A rev CF: change due to FDI: 1. FDI 146/190 24-FCP 101 8201, Node FDI Battery efficiency for high speed FACH Bit 14 added! W12 EG4 rev CG1: FDI 3/190 24-FCP 121 3051, Node FDI Improved L2 for W12 RNC introduced bit 15 use added. W12B EG4 rev CG2: change due to CR: 136/... bit-field definitions introduced W13B sprint 12W48 rev CT: change due to PSS: 83/102 68-FCP 121 7060, AMR NB MM multi-rate-set 1 Modified in W15A, Sprint 14w37, 10/..B CPI update PSS: 248/10268-FCP1217060.

parameterext.name: EVENT_PARAM_WANTED_CONNECTION_PROPERTIES_EXT
parameterext.paramextdescription: Bitmap indicating conection properties for the wanted configuration: Bit 0 indicates if Enhanced Uplink for FACH is used: 0=EUL-FACH is not used, 1=EUL-FACH is used Bit 1 indicates if IU UP version 2 is used: 0=CIU UP version 1 is used, 1=IU UPversion 2 is used Bit 2 indicates if Dynamic RLC parameter configuration is used: 0=Dynamic RLCis not used, 1=Dynamic RLC is used Bit 3 indicates if Improved MAC-is/es reordering is used: 0=Improved MAC-is/es is not used, 1=Improved MAC-is/es is used Bit 4 indicates if EUL Multi Carrier is used: 0=EUL Multi Carrier is not used, 1=EUL Multi Carrier is used Bit 5 is not used Bit 6 is not used Bit 7 indicates if Data Acceleration activation is requested: 0=Data Acceleration not requested, 1=Data Acceleration requested. Bits 8-15 are spare and are always 0. Note: No validity bit is used!
parameterext.paramextcomments: NO VALIDITY BIT IS USED! W12B EG4 rev CG1: introduced by FDI 26/190 24-FCP 121 3051 PA33, Node FDI EUL on CELL_FACH W12B EG4 rev CG2: change due to CR: 136/... bit-field definitions introduced W13B sprint 12W48 rev CT: change due to PSS: 83/102 68-FCP 121 7060, AMR NB MM multi-rate-set 1 W14B sprint 13W41 rev CZ: changed due to PSS:20/102 68-FCP 121 7060, EUL Multi Carrier W14B sprint 14W13 rev DC4: changed due to Data Accelaration, FAJ 121 3907 feature Modified in W15A, Sprint 14w37, 10/..B CPI update, PSS: 248/10268-FCP1217060.
